Preheat your #grill{} to high. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Cut the bottom off the @asparagus{200} spears and discard. Chop each spear into three pieces. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}, then slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Put a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat and add the onion. Cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @freekeh{150} and stir to combine.

Pour in the @water{300} and add the @vegetable stock powder{1/2%stock cube}. Stir to dissolve the stock pot and bring to a simmer. Turn the heat to low and pop a #lid{} on. Leave to cook for ~{15%minutes}. Once the time is up, remove the pan from the heat and leave to rest for another ~{5%minutes} (lid still on).

Meanwhile, pop the asparagus and courgette on a #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle over some oil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Grill until slightly charred, ~{10-15%minutes}. 

> Keep an eye on them and shake the tray occasionally.

When the freekeh is cooked, add the @unsalted butter{15%g} and three-quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Stir energetically. Squeeze in a little @lemon{1/2}(juiced), stir and taste. Season with salt, pepper and lemon juice accordingly. Add the veggies and carefully stir them in.

Serve the freekeh risotto in #bowls{} with the @walnuts{25} and remaining cheese sprinkled on top. Enjoy!